 Useful notes about film Black and White Development # HP5+ film # Kodak HC-110 Chemistry sheet from Kodak Unofficial HC110 Resource Developer: HC-110 One film: Place at bottom. 10 ml dev + 290 ml water Two films: 15ml dev + 450 ml water 5 minutes at 20°C. (Maybe 6:30 if 18°C) Agitate first minute, then 5 inversions every minute Stop (water or stop bath) for 1 minute Fix for 5 minutes Wash 8-10 mins Dip in photoflo Remove from spool (clean spool immediately) Photoflo - maybe optional, use distilled water.
HP5 Pushed Development times (at 20°C) with HC110 dil B:
800 - 7.5 mins 1600 - 11 mins 12800 (some crazy) 140 minutes! Agitate for 1 min, then stand for 139&hellip;
